WebService::LibraryThing::ThingISBN is a Perl interface to the
LibraryThing social cataloging website's thingISBN web service, which
"takes an ISBN and returns a list of ISBNs from the same 'work' (ie.,
other editions and translations)."

The web service is freely available for noncommercial use, per the
terms at http://www.librarything.com/api

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc WebService::LibraryThing::ThingISBN

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=WebService-LibraryThing-ThingISBN

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/WebService-LibraryThing-ThingISBN

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/WebService-LibraryThing-ThingISBN

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/WebService-LibraryThing-ThingISBN/


